{"source_key":"sha256-9c96664da244cdd50b191ef0b61ed94f","record_index":484,"record_hash":"sha256:18d6f3d3de3d9922502abb986d6d904593750583234c6553dd7ccf7a05bdaca3","timestamp":"2026-05-21T02:58:08.047Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"The pattern is pretty useful: `set_base_branch` is not one bug. It‚Äôs a junk drawer command where several repo-state failures pile up.\n\nAcross the last 30 days:\n\n| version | attempts | failures | failing users | failure rate | failures / failing user |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| `0.19.10` | 1460 | 752 | 79 | 51.5% | 9.5 |\n| `0.19.11` | 234 | 119 | 13 | 50.9% | 9.2 |\n| `0.19.12` | 320 | 96 | 12 | 30.0% | 8.0 |\n| `0.19.13` | 165 | 45 | 8 | 27.3% | 5.6 |\n\nSo: it‚Äôs improving, but failures are still sticky. Users don‚Äôt fail once; they get trapped and retry.\n\n**What changed by version**\n`0.19.10` was the ugly one:\n- `workspace_ref_missing`: **313 failures / 47 users**\n- `workspace_conflict`: **138 / 17**\n- `no_merge_base`: **65 / 9**\n- repo ownership/object corruption/missing object stuff also shows up\n\nThat smells like a real workspace-state regression or migration problem. The biggest message was:\n\n`The reference '[REDACTED:entropy]' did not exist`\n\nThat mostly disappears after `0.19.10`, which suggests it was fixed or the affected cohort aged out.\n\n`0.19.11` is smaller but still bad:\n- `workspace_conflict`: **66 / 11**\n- `unsupported extension name extensions.relativeworktrees`: **50 / 1**\n\nSo `0.19.11` still had workspace integration problems, plus one user hammering a Git feature we didn‚Äôt support well.\n\n`0.19.12` shifts into edge cases:\n- empty/unborn branches: **55 / 3**\n- missing remotes: **17 / 2**\n- no merge-base: **6 / 2**\n\nThat‚Äôs less ‚Äúwe broke workspace refs‚Äù and more ‚Äúuser selected a base branch in a weird repo state.‚Äù\n\n`0.19.13` is mostly concentrated:\n- CodeCommit remote-helper URL parse: **24 / 1**\n- no merge-base: **16 / 2**\n- workspace conflict: **2 / 2**\n- local repo path / unsafe ownership: tiny\n\nSo latest is not a broad regression. It‚Äôs a few repo states repeatedly failing.\n\n**Main lessons**\n1. `0.19.10` had the real scary pattern: missing `gitbutler/workspace` ref and workspace conflicts across many users.\n2. Newer versions mostly fail on valid-but-weird Git setups: unrelated histories, empty branches, missing remotes, CodeCommit helper URLs.\n3. Attempt-based failure rate exaggerates the problem. Distinct failing users is the better signal.\n4. `error_code = Unknown` is costing us. These should be typed: `WorkspaceRefMissing`, `NoMergeBaseWithTarget`, `InvalidRemoteUrl`, `UnbornBranch`, `RemoteMissing`, etc.\n5. The CodeCommit case is a real compatibility fix: don‚Äôt require `gix` to parse the remote URL just to set the base branch.\n\nMy pick: fix CodeCommit parsing first, then add typed errors around merge-base / unborn branch / workspace ref missing. That gives us both fewer failures and much sharper PostHog signal next release.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-21T02:58:08.047Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}